identifier: The Five-Year Transportation Program (5YTP) is an annual document listing road and bridge projects planned for the next five years. ?A snapshot of 5YTP projects is produced annually and presented for approval to the State Transportation Commission. ?The 5YTP snapshot is later archived and the document is posted on MDOT?s Web site. ?A Web-based interactive state map is available which plots individual projects for the public to easily view.
